<TITLE> Alleged terrorist held by local people in Barisal town </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, Sept 27 (bdnews24.com)Local people in the town caught red-handed an alleged terrorist, Saiful Islam Tuhin, when he tried to gun down two people at dusk on Saturday, police said. Police and witnesses alleged Tuhin first tried to gun down Sultan Ahmed, a stenographer at Barisal joint district judge's court. But after an abortive bid to kill him, he attempted to shot Habibur Rahman Mintu, an UP member, who tried to stop him from his shooting spree. Barisal Kotwali police chief Nuruzzaman Chowdhury said Saiful Islam Tuhin, a notorious terrorist, was immediately taken into custody. Tuhin is the son of Lutfar Rahman from Bakerganj. The incident occurred near Raipasha Mollabarhi Mosque in Bosirhat area under sadar upazila. Police seized a motorcycle, a nine mm pistol and three rounds of ammunition from the spot. bdn
